HEADWORD: Fetis
<hw>Fe"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>fetis</ets>,
<ets>faitis</ets>. Cf. <er>Factitious</er>.]</ety> <def>Neat; pretty;
well made; graceful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Full <qex>fetis</qex> was her cloak, as I was ware.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fetisely</ent>⟦br⟧
